cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with minimisation of weighted and probabilistic automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a polynomial-time minimisation algorithm for weighted automata. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses an application in image compression. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as probabilistic automata are commonly used in machine learning. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper studies the complexity of the minimisation problem for probabilistic automata.
